<subSubSection id="C30B4193FFBAFFBAFF74880C8925A60F" pageId="1" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAE1218FFBAFFBAFF74880C8925A60F" blockId="1.[174,1233,997,1376]" pageId="1" pageNumber="12">
Description (based on 4 mature specimens). Body elongated (
<figureCitation id="132A0E9DFFBAFFBAFC3C880C8BE2A70F" box="[939,997,1094,1120]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1176,1198]" captionTargetBox="[193,1205,174,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-212@2.[193,1205,174,1154]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. General view of the trematodes found in the corncrake in Ukraine: Brachylaima fuscata (A), Prosthogonimus ovatus (B), Prosthogonimus cuneatus (C). Scale bars 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377538/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="12">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, A), with maximum width 476–542 anterior to ventral sucker; body length 
<geoCoordinate id="EE2574DFFFBAFFBAFCBF882C8B6EA7EF" box="[808,873,1126,1152]" degrees="2,487" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="1" pageNumber="12" precision="55" value="2.487">2,487</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE2574DFFFBAFFBAFCFE882C8BBEA7EF" box="[873,953,1126,1152]" degrees="2,849" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="1" pageNumber="12" precision="55" value="-2.849">–2,849</geoCoordinate>
. Oral sucker larger than ventral sucker. Oral sucker 241–288×211–282. Ventral sucker 150–182×145–180. Distance from anterior end of body to centre of ventral sucker 890–960. Pharynx well-developed, round, 102–174×123–168. Gonads in posterior quarter of body. Ovary between testes. Anterior testis 160–272×167–261, posterior testis 164–269×122–245. Ovary 131–162×136– 171. Vitellarium distributed in two lateral fields, extending from posterior extremity of ventral sucker to level of anterior edge of anterior testis. Eggs oval, numerous, 28–35× 
<quantity id="4CE9BFFDFFBAFFBAFB32896C88EEA60F" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" metricValueMax="4.572" metricValueMin="4.064" pageId="1" pageNumber="12" unit="in" value="17.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="16.0">16– 18 in</quantity>
size.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
